text.text:
- Oversee the strategic, administrative, operational, and financial activities of the Social Media Department.

- Responsible for the data-driven development and execution of social media strategy for the Mount Sinai Health System and the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. 

- In alignment with the goals of the Marketing and Communications Department, develop a strategic framework for engaging patients, physicians, staff, and medical students. 

-Deploy social media programs in support of Mount Sinai’s digital reputation. 

- Establish strategic partnerships with organizations to foster growth through co-branded social media events and campaigns. 

- Focus on increasing follower growth and engagement rates across all social media channels to maintain Top 5 national and regional hospital social media rankings.

text.accessibilityText: Associate Director, Digital and Social Media

text.text:
- Develop and manage social media profiles on Facebook, Twitter, YouTube, LinkedIn, Pinterest, and other similar community sites for the Mount Sinai Health System, its member hospitals and the Icahn School of Medicine
- Manage content calendars and leverage social media platforms and audiences to promote content for several WordPress blog sites
- Write, produce, and distribute numerous posts per day to promote service areas, physicians, nurses, students, leadership, events, research, and initiatives
- Create and edit images and social graphics using Adobe Photoshop and  other advanced software platforms
- Analyze follower, engagements and usage trends for social media profiles, blogs, and recommend improvements
- Maintain knowledge and awareness of best practices and developments in social media and management platforms, and make recommendations to promote continuous improvement and innovation
- Analyze website information, including usage trends and statistics and recommend related improvements to social media strategies
- Enforce and update social media guidelines and policy to use as a reference point in responding to requests
- Provide guidance to interns and approve their work for public posting
- Collaborate with programs/departments who wish to create their own individual social media presence to evaluate their current social media strategies, and provide advice and support when needed
- Provide stakeholders with social media training as needed
- Attend and promote events in real-time and assists stakeholders with social media publicity opportunities, like Tweet Chats
- Monitor high profile reputation management requests routinely, and in crisis situations
- Assist with social media strategy and goal setting

subtitle.text: Commitee Member, Digital and Social · Jun 2020 - Present
subtitle.accessibilityText: Commitee Member, Digital and Social · Jun 2020 - Present

text.text:
As Director of Digital and Social Media, Chloe A. Politis oversees all strategic, operational, and financial social media-related activities for the Mount Sinai Health System. Her data-driven approach has resulted in a 27 percent increase in followers, 370 percent increase in engagement, and 66 percent increase in video views across the Health System’s social accounts. Under Chloe’s leadership, Mount Sinai has maintained a top ranking in social media for health care systems in the New York metropolitan area for 8 years.
 
Chloe leads a four-person team that consults on the social media efforts of more than 200 departments. The team recruited, trained, and deployed more than 300 physicians from a variety of specialties for their social media ambassador program. In addition to increasing brand recognition, the program addresses the rampant medical misinformation proliferating online.
 
At the start of the COVID-19 crisis, the team launched a highly successful communications campaign that generated millions of video views across Facebook and Youtube. The campaign was awarded Best COVID-19 Pandemic Communications at the eHealthcare Leadership Awards.
 
Chloe has a BA in English from Fordham University, an MA in Health Advocacy from Sarah Lawrence College, and a certificate in Digital Marketing from Columbia University Business School. She is a contributor to Forbes.com and a member of the Forbes Communication Council.

When Chloe isn’t scrolling through social media, she volunteers as a Braven Leadership Coach, where she empowers first-generation college students like herself with the professional skills, confidence, experiences and networks to boldly thrive in today’s competitive world.
